input.content:
# @belt/core

Plugin system with tapable hooks for Belt developer toolkit.

## Install

```bash
npm install @belt/core
```

## Usage

```typescript
import { createBelt, type BeltPlugin } from '@belt/core';

const belt = createBelt({ rootDir: process.cwd() });

// Use existing plugins
belt.use(somePlugin());

// Run checks
const results = await belt.check();
```

## Creating Plugins

```typescript
import type { BeltPlugin } from '@belt/core';

export function myPlugin(): BeltPlugin {
  return {
    name: 'my-plugin',
    apply(belt) {
      belt.hooks.initialize.tapPromise('my-plugin', async (ctx) => {
        // Setup
      });

      belt.hooks.beforeCheck.tapPromise('my-plugin', async (ctx) => {
        // Pre-check logic
      });

      belt.hooks.checkResults.tapPromise('my-plugin', async (ctx, results) => {
        // Process results
        return results;
      });
    },
  };
}
```

## Available Hooks

| Hook | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `initialize` | Called once during setup |
| `beforeCheck` | Before running checks |
| `checkResults` | Process check results |
| `afterCheck` | After checks complete |
| `registerCommands` | Register CLI commands |
| `beforeCommand` | Before command execution |
| `afterCommand` | After command execution |
| `log` | Intercept log messages |
| `shutdown` | Cleanup on exit |

## License

MIT

